{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":92376,"duration_api_ms":92344,"num_turns":8,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"0747f27f-b90e-4ce3-913e-cb44a5cb1d75","total_cost_usd":0.4295145,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":40730,"cache_read_input_tokens":144094,"output_tokens":4115,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":40730,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":6,"outputTokens":4115,"cacheReadInputTokens":144094,"cacheCreationInputTokens":40730,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.4295145,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"rulings":[{"amendment_id":"fr-14-ab7143b0","decision":"reject","rationale":"The dispute hinges on whether plan_hash should be auto-populated from the milestone snapshot at row creation time versus deferred via safe_plan_hash_backfill(). After examining the code, both approaches share the same fundamental race condition: if persist_plan() runs between bead dispatch and record_task_run_start(), the snapshot read at creation time captures the wrong plan version regardless of when it is written to plan_hash. The deferred backfill does not eliminate this race — it only provides a narrow safety net when the plan evolves again after creation (causing a mismatch that prevents writing the wrong value). Reviewer 2's internal-consistency argument is logically compelling: the code trusts the creation snapshot for deferred backfill but refuses to trust it at creation time. However, the planner's core principle — that no attribution is preferable to wrong attribution — is the stronger design invariant. Wrong plan_hash values are silent data integrity violations that propagate through lineage queries without detection, while missing plan_hash values are visible gaps that can be flagged and handled. The deferred approach, while only marginally safer, does provide a real probabilistic guard against the race condition scenario, and the tests at the cited lines deliberately encode this conservative invariant rather than locking in a regression. The spec-code discrepancy should be resolved via fr-14-cb88579a (spec reconciliation) rather than by restoring auto-population."}],"summary":"Rejected the single disputed amendment (fr-14-ab7143b0). The amendment proposed restoring snapshot-based plan_hash auto-population on new running rows. While reviewer 2's argument about internal logical inconsistency between creation-time refusal and deferred backfill acceptance is technically sound, the planner's core design principle prevails: no attribution is safer than potentially wrong attribution. Wrong plan_hash values are silent data integrity violations, while missing values are visible gaps. The deferred backfill provides a marginal but real safety net against the persist_plan() race condition, and the updated test expectations deliberately encode this conservative invariant. The spec-implementation discrepancy should be resolved through formal spec reconciliation (fr-14-cb88579a) rather than code changes."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"f9566b7a-17e5-469b-b0dc-fbcc0fa24a99"}
